  "prompt": "What is the essay asked in civil service main exam in 2002?",
  "response": "The Civil Services Main Examination essay paper for 2002 included several topics from which candidates could choose to write an essay. The topics were as follows:\n\n1. Modern technological education and human values.\n2. Search for truth can only be a spiritual problem.\n3. If youth knew, if age could.\n4. The paths of glory lead but to the grave.\n5. The pursuit of excellence.\n6. Empowerment alone cannot help our women.\n\nCandidates were required to select one of these topics and compose an essay that reflected their understanding, insights, and ability to articulate their thoughts coherently and persuasively.",
